# Backend Server Module

## PURPOSE
Node.js/Express server for user management, payment processing, and data persistence.
Provides REST API for extension to manage accounts, payments, and subscription tracking.

## STRUCTURE
- /routes: API endpoint handlers
- /models: Database schemas and models
- /middleware: Auth, validation, error handling
- /config: Configuration files
- /utils: Helper functions

## CONTAINS
- server.js: Main Express application
- Database connection setup
- API routes for users, payments, subscriptions
- Authentication middleware (JWT)
- Payment integration (Stripe)

## RESPONSIBILITIES
- User registration and authentication
- JWT token generation and validation
- Payment processing ($5 lifetime access)
- Track user payment status and run count
- Store user subscription data
- Enforce free tier limits (5 subs)
- Rate limiting and security

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /.windsurf (root context)
- Called by: /src/api/* (frontend API client)
- Modules: /backend/routes/.windsurf, /backend/models/.windsurf

## RULES
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Validate all inputs
- Use HTTPS only in production
- Implement proper error handling
- Log all payment transactions
- Secure JWT tokens with strong secrets
- Use bcrypt for password hashing
